                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Side effects to monitor:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li>Sleep disruption (if taken too late or dose too high)</li>
                    <li>Decreased appetite</li>
                    <li>Possible jitteriness</li>
                    <li>Headaches or dry mouth</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Safety warnings:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li>Do not exceed prescribed dose</li>
                    <li>Take breaks on weekends to prevent tolerance</li>
                    <li>Communicate with therapist about dose adjustments</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Rationale:</strong> Vyvanse offers subtle, sustained effect. Increasing dose may provide all-day support, reducing need for additional stimulants like Adderall.</p>
            </div>

