                <p><strong>Dosage:</strong> 5mg</p>
                <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>Timing:</strong> Take in the morning with Vyvanse OR as needed (PRN) in the afternoon</p>
                <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Provides stronger, immediate boost in motivation and energy</p>
                
                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>How to take:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li>Take as prescribed, not more than directed</li>
                    <li>Can be taken with or without food</li>
                    <li>Use as needed (PRN) for extra focus when required</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Expected benefits:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li>Quick onset of focus and energy</li>
                    <li>Immediate boost for important tasks or meetings</li>
                    <li>Helps with initial morning motivation</li>
                    <li>Works within 30-60 minutes</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Side effects to monitor:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li>Sleep issues if taken too late in the day</li>
                    <li>Increased heart rate</li>
                    <li>Possible anxiety or jitteriness</li>
                    <li>Crash when it wears off (4-6 hours)</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Safety warnings:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li>Use only as needed; avoid taking late in day</li>
                    <li>Do not increase frequency without consulting therapist</li>
                    <li>Monitor for signs of psychological dependency</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top:15px;"><strong>Rationale:</strong> Adderall is reserved for times when extra focus is required, preventing overuse and dependency. As Vyvanse dose optimizes, Adderall becomes PRN rather than daily.</p>
            </div>

